 output at 662 keV, from 6.3 to 4.9%, and from 44,000 to 52,000 ph/MeV,\nrespectively. The method, in addition to improving NaI performance, provides a\nversatile framework for rapidly unveiling complex and concealed correlations\nbetween material composition and performance, and should be broadly applicable\nto optimization of other material properties.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 24 Apr 2015 23:28:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-08-25"}
